Norwegian-Swedish Agreement being signed in London. The NorwegianForeign Minister –Mr. Trygve Lie, and the Swedish Minister accredited to the Norwegian Government-Baron Johan Beck-Friis, yesterday signed an agreement between the Norwegian and Swedish governments concerning the payments in connection with Swedish deliveries for reconstruction purposes in Norway after the war. The deliveries will include foodstuffs, seeds, iron and steel produce, as well as medicines. In addition a Protocol concerning the initiation of discussions regarding the future economic relations between the two countries was also signed. Picture shows Baron Johan Beck-Friis (left) and Minister Trygve Lie signing the agreement in the Norwegian Foreign Ministry. London 14.4.44.
